    { question: "How might the ICJ ruling affect national climate policies and corporate responsibility?", answer: "The ICJ ruling is expected to increase pressure on governments to adopt more ambitious climate targets and policies. It also provides a stronger legal basis for climate litigation against states and corporations, potentially leading to increased accountability for environmental damage and accelerated decarbonization efforts." },
    { question: "What can individuals and communities do to address the escalating climate emergency?", answer: "Individuals can reduce their carbon footprint through sustainable consumption, supporting renewable energy, and advocating for climate action. Communities can implement local adaptation strategies, invest in green infrastructure, and push for robust climate policies from their local and national governments." }
