    risks: ["Bitcoin volatility makes it unsuitable for real estate pricing in most markets.", "Regulatory action against Ripple or celebrity-linked crypto campaigns.", "Continued vulnerability of DeFi protocols to front-running and MEV attacks.", "Overreliance on Bitcoin as a hedge in portfolios without proper risk management.", "Social engineering and scams targeting retail investors influenced by celebrity endorsements."],
    opportunities: ["Increased adoption of Bitcoin in high-inflation economies as a unit of account.", "Growth of audited, secure DeFi platforms that mitigate MEV risks.", "Institutional adoption of crypto as a portfolio diversifier.", "Philanthropic crypto projects that drive real-world impact and improve public perception.", "Regulatory clarity leading to broader mainstream acceptance."],
    outlook: "The coming months will determine whether these flashpoints represent growing pains or systemic risks. Fidelity’s Bitcoin pricing thesis may gain traction in select markets, but widespread adoption is unlikely without stability. The DeFi exploit serves as a reminder that while innovation is rapid, security lags behind. Celebrity campaigns, though influential, are unlikely to sustain long-term adoption without tangible utility. For Indian investors, the key is to remain vigilant, prioritize education, and avoid being swayed by hype or fear.",
    conclusion: "This week’s crypto developments—from Fidelity’s unconventional affordability narrative to the Jaredfromsubway heist and Matt Damon’s Ripple-linked charity—paint a picture of an ecosystem in flux. Bitcoin’s potential role in redefining asset pricing, the constant evolution of DeFi threats, and the strategic use of celebrity influence all reflect a market searching for legitimacy. For investors, the lesson is clear: opportunity and risk are two sides of the same coin. Success will favor those who combine curiosity with caution, innovation with integrity.",
