      probabilityWeightedOutlook: "There\'s a moderate to high probability (60%) that \'Open Standard\' will successfully launch and gain significant institutional traction, becoming a top-tier stablecoin for regulated entities. However, the probability of it fully supplanting Tether or Circle\'s dominance in the broader crypto market is low (20%), suggesting a more fragmented but institutionally robust stablecoin landscape. There\'s a 20% chance of significant regulatory or competitive roadblocks hindering its widespread adoption.",
