      bearCase: "The bearish case argues that \'AI jitters\' signal an impending correction in overvalued tech stocks. Samsung\'s cautious outlook could be a harbinger of broader industry headwinds, including increased competition, slower enterprise adoption, or regulatory challenges. A global economic slowdown could exacerbate these issues, leading to a more prolonged downturn in high-growth sectors.",
      neutralCase: "A neutral stance suggests that the market is in a phase of re-evaluation and consolidation. While AI remains a powerful long-term trend, the initial speculative fervor is giving way to more discerning investment. This period will likely see continued sector rotation, regional divergences, and a focus on companies demonstrating tangible earnings growth and sustainable business models, rather than just hype.",
